{
  "stem": "19895.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 16.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they said that he should be put on a-- a kind of a makeshift stretcher.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they took him away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they said to me, try to get better.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Try to-- try to, not to lay down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because the more you lay down, the weaker you get.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again, next day, I was trying to join the labor unit.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I didn't see Tomas Stern for awhile.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then couple of days later, I was at the end of my rope.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was extremely weak.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was ill.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't know what-- you know, exhaustion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and bone-- skin and bone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I must have lost weight beyond recognition.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they took me to the same location where I found Tomas Stern.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was a small barrack where there was heat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had a stove.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in that location, there were Jewish doctors who, with minimal, minimal medical equipment-- whatever they had in they physician handbags when they were taken away-- they were performing surgery.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They amputated legs and wrapped them in all kind of rags and dirty papers and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because the infection which took place from that frozen and-- and-- and diseased extremity, the only solution was to try to amputate it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And how do you amputate?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was no local anesthesia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there-- I'm talking somewhat of a specialist-- retroactive about it there, because I'm an anesthesiologist by medical training, which I did in the United States for 35 years just in practice, and so on, which we'll talk about later.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So these people were operated on just until they fainted from pain.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I do know of one person whose amputation apparently saved him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because when I returned to Budapest, and a couple of months later, I bumped into him on his crutches.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He survived.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
